broken blossoms is a 1936 british drama film directed by john brahm and starring emlyn williams , arthur margetson , basil radford and edith sharpe . director bernard vorhaus was technical supervisor . the film is based on the short story " the chink and the child " by thomas burke from his collection limehouse nights ( 1916 ) , and was produced at twickenham studios in london . the story had previously been adapted by d. w. griffith for his film broken blossoms ( 1919 ) starring lillian gish .